      Duration ModelI.getNextTimeAdvance()
      return the duration until the next internal event as previously computed by timeAdvance() but in a side effect free manner.
      Duration ModelI.timeAdvance()
      return the time the simulated system remains in the current state before making a transition to the next sequential state; the method must be implemented by the user in each atomic model.
      Methods in fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.models.interfaces with parameters of type Duration 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description

      do a confluent transition i.e., processing internal and external transitions occurring at the same simulation time using previously stored external input events.
      void ModelI.externalTransition(Duration elapsedTime)
      do the next external transition, both calling the method userDefinedExternalTransition and doing all of the necessary internal catering work.
      void ModelI.showCurrentState(java.lang.String indent, Duration elapsedTime)
      show the current state of the model during the simulation.

      show the current state of the model during the simulation.
      void ModelI.userDefinedCausalTransition(Duration elapsedTime)
      perform a causal transition; this method is user model-dependent hence must be implemented by the user for atomic models; the user implementation should not change any of the implementation related variables.
      void ModelI.userDefinedConfluentTransition(Duration elapsedTime)
      do a confluent transition i.e., processing internal and external transitions occurring at the same simulation time using previously stored external input events; this method is user-model-dependent hence must be implemented by the user for atomic models.
      void ModelI.userDefinedExternalTransition(Duration elapsedTime)
      do an external transition using a previously stored external input event; this method is user-model-dependent hence must be implemented by the user for atomic models; the user implementation should not change any of the implementation related variables.
      void ModelI.userDefinedInternalTransition(Duration elapsedTime)
      perform an internal transition; this method is user model-dependent hence must be implemented by the user for atomic models; the user implementation should not change any of the implementation related variables.

      void SimulatorI.confluentEventStep(Duration elapsedTime)
      process an external input event or an internal event at the given simulated time which must correspond to the current value of the simulated time clock at the time of the call; when more than on event can be executed, only one is chosen and executed.
      void SimulatorI.externalEventStep(Duration elapsedTime)
      process an external input event at a simulated time which must correspond to the current value of the global simulated time clock at the time of the call i.e., the sum of the time of the last event in this engine and the given elapsed time.
